+								*Exxx*
+			A closure is actually an unnamed function similar to
+			|lambda| with the internal name starting with
+			"<closure>" instead of "<lambda>".  In the above
+			example, the Funcref to the closure is set to a local
+			variable "Bar".  A closure is a local function because
+			it uses local variables of the outer function, thus
+			it cannot have a prefix "s:" nor "g:".
 
 						*function-search-undo*
 			The last used search pattern and the redo command "."
